# Architecture

Single .NET solution for the Windows print relay tray app. Parent platform owns API and badge rendering.

## Directory map

| Path | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `src/EventPlatform.PrintRelay.Core/` | API client, setup code, poll loop, settings, logging — **no Windows UI** |
| `src/EventPlatform.PrintRelay.App/` | Tray app, wizard, WebView2 print host (Phase 1–2) — Windows only |
| `src/EventPlatform.PrintRelay.Spike/` | Gate 3 CLI; regression until App owns print path |
| `tests/EventPlatform.PrintRelay.Core.Tests/` | xUnit + JSON Schema contract tests |
| `schemas/` | Pinned platform JSON Schema + fixtures (`platform-pin.json`) |
| `docs/` | PRD, spike runbook, staging integration |

## Boundaries

| Concern | Owner |
|---|---|
| Print queue API, `badge_html` rendering | **event-management-platform** |
| Tray app, MSI, WebView2 silent print | **this repo** |
| Node relay (macOS/Linux) | **event-management-platform** `/tools/print-relay` |

## Layering

1. **Core** — HTTP, decode setup code, poll backoff, job state machine, settings persistence interfaces.
2. **App / Spike** — WinForms UI, `WebView2SilentPrinter`, tray, toasts.
3. **No badge layout** in any layer — consume `badge_html` string only.

